post_text:
Good evening families,

With feedback and guidance from leadership teams consisting of staff and parents we are putting the final touches on our official plans for reopening schools on August 12th.

The news released from Gov. Newsom today has helped provide additional guidance to finalize these plans and maintain our goal of opening on August 12th with the safest options available. We will be communicating the details to all Redding School District families on Wednesday July 22nd.

Thank you and please have a restful and safe weekend.

Robert Adams
Superintendent

Classified Employee Appreciation Week - May 17th - 23rd

Superintendent Rob Adams message to Classified Employees; "I am giving another shout out to our wonderful classified workers who are still serving or looking for ways to serve. A huge thanks to food service workers, custodians, office staff, instructional support aides, after school personnel to name a few. All of our classified staff are invited to a distance celebration and treats giveaway at the District Office Drive by Event from 1:00 pm to 2:30 pm on May 21, 2020. Please come in your cars and our administrative staff will have the chance to give you a gift and celebrate your commitment to our district. Location: 5885 East Bonnyview Redding 96001."

It‚Äôs easy to be positive when everything is going great. Real optimism, faith and leadership are revealed in how you respond to adversity.

Today let's:

1. Stay positive.
2. Be thankful.
3. Choose faith over fear.
4. Replace "Have to" with "Get To."
5. Encourage others.
6. Use this time to learn, improve and grow.

-Jon Gordon

Good Evening,

We just wanted to send a quick announcement that although a statewide ‚Äúshelter in place‚Äù has been issued, essential services like our drive through food service will still be operating for our community. We are taking into consideration the more stringent standards and reducing staff where we can without compromising the offer of drive through meals for our families.

We will still be operational tomorrow Friday 03/20, and not only that, due to a generous donation from local restaurants like Moonstone Bistro we will have fresh salads at our Manzanita and Turtle Bay locations to go with lunch tomorrow!

Thanks is everyone, see you in line! ü§©ü§©

post_text:
Good Afternoon Families, This is Superintendent Adams

The online resources will be available shortly but let me first offer you a phone number to call if you do not have online access. Call this number and the person will gather some information in order for us to print a packet for your child. Your child's school site will then call you when it is ready for pick up. If you are in need of this support please call... 225-0085. M-F 7:30am - 4:30pm

In order to access the online enrichment resources go to any school district website and in the header you will see a button called Enrichment. The page location is here, http://reddingschools.net/online-enrichment This will take you to resources for you to use during the day with your child. Please continue to monitor district updates by using the news button in the header or by subscribing to our Facebook page. We will continue to update as information unfolds.

Take care and be well,
Rob Adams
Superintendent

post_text:
On Sunday, March 15, 2020, Governor Newsom issued more strict guidance on public activities in the state of California due to the COVID-19 pandemic. In light of this new information, we have updated our planning and we are suspending all instruction, services, and public access at all of the Redding School District Schools. We apologize for
such late notice but we will be closed to the public while our staff makes plans for supporting your children for the time that classes are suspended from March 16th to April 3rd. Spring Break is scheduled for April 6th through 13th with classes scheduled to begin on the 14th. Please stay tuned for updates from your school within this coming week of how we will support your child's learning while classes are
suspended.

Rob Adams
Superintendent

Mrs. Wiseman Sequoia Schools Band Director shared the following about the CMEA Competition, which was held at Shasta College in the Music Department on Saturday, March 7th.

‚ÄúHats off to the wonderful String program and their awesome showing on Saturday. Some of these same students and others also competed in the Band solos and ensembles. We had 3 solos and 6 ensembles compete and 2 received and excellent rating and 7 received #1, Superior rating. We had two solos receive command performance. Congratulations to Joe and Evie! It was a fantastic day, all around and our students represented Sequoia so well. The judges commented on the quality of music coming out of Sequoia Music program. Thanks to the parents who also gave up their Saturday to bring and support their kids. We could not be prouder of the Sequoia Music Family.‚Äù

Congratulations, Shannon Osborne!

Shared by Mr. Anderson, Turtle Bay School Principal; ‚ÄúIt is with great joy that I have the opportunity to announce that Shannon Osborne has been nominated for the Redding Rotary Teacher of the Year!

This past year, Shannon was asked to move from the 1st Grade to 8th Grade, which would be a daunting task for any teacher. Shannon approached this with a positive attitude and as an opportunity to help the school and the Jr. High team, and she has exceeded all expectations. When speaking to her colleagues and staff, everyone mentioned how Shannon is always willing to go above and beyond the call of duty for her students and to make a positive impact on our school. The job she did as Athletic Director and now Teacher-In-Charge has been phenomenal.

Congratulations, Shannon! You are truly deserving of this honor.‚Äù

World Read Aloud Day is February 5th, 2020
Bonny View will be participating with schools around the World in World Read Aloud Day. Lit World founded World Read Aloud Day (WRAD) in 2010 because reading aloud is a powerful and transformative act. They will have guest readers on campus, pop-up reading stations, and more. They will participate in a live stream of a campus-wide shared read aloud called After the Fall by Dan Santat. The book will be read by a community member and be streamed to the Redding School District Youtube channel. If you would like to be a volunteer reader please contact the school. Happy Reading!
https://www.litworld.org/worldreadaloudday

text:
World Read Aloud Day is February 5th, 2020
Bonny View will be participating with schools around the World in World Read Aloud Day. Lit World founded World Read Aloud Day (WRAD) in 2010 because reading aloud is a powerful and transformative act. They will have guest readers on campus, pop-up reading stations, and more. They will participate in a live stream of a campus-wide shared read aloud called After the Fall by Dan Santat. The book will be read by a community member and be streamed to the Redding School District Youtube channel. If you would like to be a volunteer reader please contact the school. Happy Reading!
https://www.litworld.org/worldreadaloudday

post_text:
Book Tasting 2019

Tricia Tompkins and Kim Wards 4th & 5th Grade Classes at Bonny View School participated in a Book Tasting today Wednesday, December 18th.

What is a book tasting you ask? It is an opportunity to preview books and come up with a ‚Äúmust read‚Äù list of books. The students preview the cover, read the back cover, read a few pages, then fill out their menu and rate the book. The students have discussions at their group about the book and share what they liked or disliked about the book they ‚Äòtasted‚Äô. At the end of the experience, they write a reflection about the book tasting.

They also are served yummy snacks and hot apple cider to enjoy during their book tasting experience. What a fun way to find a few good books to read over the Winter Recess!

Hello everyone!!!
I wanted to let you know about our new RSD MUSIC Merchandise that is available now!!
For those of you who don't know, we held a contest for students to make their own original T-shirt, Hoodie, and Beanie designs. Students then were able to vote online for their favorite design. The winners for each category get their design printed and sold to help support the RSD MUSIC programs.

Here is a link to the website for ordering:

http://www.edfirstredding.org/new-products

Make sure to get your orders in by Thursday 12-19-19 as this is a

one-time-only print! Don‚Äôt miss out!

Thanks to all the students who turned in a design! Good Job everyone!

And a big thank you to Seth Hemken for getting this all set up online!

J.J. Wilder
Music Teacher
